one of my very smartest
friends came

00:44:35.856 --> 00:44:37.766 A:middle
up with this idea of settings.

00:44:38.356 --> 00:44:39.496 A:middle
And what are settings?

00:44:39.496 --> 00:44:42.226 A:middle
Well, settings are
tunable values, right?

00:44:42.226 --> 00:44:45.526 A:middle
You take all of the settings
that you might want to tune

00:44:45.876 --> 00:44:48.226 A:middle
and put them in just an object

00:44:48.226 --> 00:44:50.106 A:middle
that just is a bag
of properties.

00:44:50.586 --> 00:44:53.276 A:middle
You use KVO, so that
when you change one

00:44:53.276 --> 00:44:56.966 A:middle
of those properties the parts of
the system that are interested

00:44:56.966 --> 00:45:00.626 A:middle
in those values changing
can know about it.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:44:56.966 --> 00:45:00.626 A:middle
in those values changing
can know about it.

00:45:00.886 --> 00:45:02.266 A:middle
She also came up
with this way to save

00:45:02.266 --> 00:45:06.036 A:middle
and restore these options,
and then there was also a way

00:45:06.036 --> 00:45:08.016 A:middle
that you could have
settings, which own settings,

00:45:08.016 --> 00:45:10.766 A:middle
which own settings, so you
could have a tree of settings.

00:45:11.026 --> 00:45:12.426 A:middle
And also came up
with an editing UI,

00:45:12.606 --> 00:45:14.226 A:middle
and it's the editing
UI I want to show you.

00:45:14.226 --> 00:45:16.866 A:middle
So here's just a very simple
example, a very simple app

00:45:17.536 --> 00:45:19.966 A:middle
that lets you manipulate
geometric shapes.

00:45:20.046 --> 00:45:23.076 A:middle
So I've got now one blue
circle, and you can go

00:45:23.076 --> 00:45:27.556 A:middle
and with the settings UI you
can then bring up a hud right

00:45:27.556 --> 00:45:31.936 A:middle
in the app, twiddle a
couple of sliders and change

00:45:31.966 --> 00:45:35.866 A:middle
from one blue triangle to
three red triangles, great.

00:45:37.106 --> 00:45:39.006 A:middle
And then similarly we
can go to this other one

00:45:39.006 --> 00:45:41.446 A:middle
that actually support
those nested settings,

00:45:41.446 --> 00:45:44.726 A:middle
that would use sort of iPhone
style, side-to-side navigation

00:45:44.726 --> 00:45:46.626 A:middle
to show you the different
levels of settings.

00:45:46.906 --> 00:45:49.086 A:middle
And so if I take the red
triangles and move it back

00:45:49.086 --> 00:45:52.146 A:middle
to the settings for the
blue circle, you have this.

00:45:52.196 --> 00:45:53.416 A:middle
And so what did this do?

00:45:53.416 --> 00:45:54.806 A:middle
This did something
very important.

00:45:55.176 --> 00:45:56.816 A:middle
This reduced iteration time

00:45:56.816 --> 00:46:01.046 A:middle
because once you had the right
settings surfaced in the app,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:45:56.816 --> 00:46:01.046 A:middle
because once you had the right
settings surfaced in the app,

00:46:01.526 --> 00:46:03.476 A:middle
you could sit with the
designer, an engineer could sit

00:46:03.476 --> 00:46:06.946 A:middle
with the designer, and try
many, many, many options.

00:46:07.536 --> 00:46:10.886 A:middle
And so we got to the point where
you kind of tried to figure

00:46:10.886 --> 00:46:12.326 A:middle
out what control
center could look like,

00:46:12.326 --> 00:46:13.556 A:middle
and the designer
could say, well,

00:46:13.556 --> 00:46:15.146 A:middle
what if we made it
2 percent darker?

00:46:15.146 --> 00:46:18.636 A:middle
I don't even know if you can
see that up on the big screen?

00:46:18.636 --> 00:46:22.316 A:middle
It's the point of it, is that
we were trying to get tuning

00:46:22.806 --> 00:46:26.356 A:middle
to this level, 2 percent
darker, 2 percent darker

00:46:26.576 --> 00:46:30.046 A:middle
on your left than on your right.

00:46:31.196 --> 00:46:34.066 A:middle
We wanted that level
of polish and attention

00:46:34.066 --> 00:46:37.416 A:middle
to every single value in the OS.

00:46:37.826 --> 00:46:40.476 A:middle
So when we had a tuning
session like this, it was great

00:46:40.476 --> 00:46:45.236 A:middle
because I could just go back to
my desk now, copy the defaults

00:46:45.236 --> 00:46:47.516 A:middle
that got saved from
the tuning session,

00:46:47.806 --> 00:46:50.266 A:middle
copy those to the new
defaults, and commit.

00:46:50.266 --> 00:46:54.696 A:middle
It's great, and this made
it cheap and easy to tune;

00:46:54.696 --> 00:46:57.626 A:middle
we could just do it over and
over and over and over again.

00:46:58.556 --> 00:47:01.966 A:middle
And this was the way that we
wound up with just a handful


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:46:58.556 --> 00:47:01.966 A:middle
And this was the way that we
wound up with just a handful

00:47:01.966 --> 00:47:03.476 A:middle
of blur styles for iOS 7

00:47:03.476 --> 00:47:04.946 A:middle
that are used consistently
everywhere.

00:47:05.366 --> 00:47:08.086 A:middle
It was very, very difficult
to come up with those,

00:47:08.086 --> 00:47:09.476 A:middle
with that set of blur styles.

00:47:09.726 --> 00:47:12.496 A:middle
And this is how we did it by
just iterating and iterating

00:47:12.496 --> 00:47:15.226 A:middle
and making iterating
easy and cheap.

00:47:15.576 --> 00:47:16.926 A:middle
The lesson really, right,

00:47:16.926 --> 00:47:19.436 A:middle
is iterating quickly
leads to better work.

00:47:19.546 --> 00:47:24.106 A:middle
I think my experience from
iOS 7 was there was a direct

00:47:24.106 --> 00:47:29.306 A:middle
correlation between how easy we
made it to try out new things

00:47:29.556 --> 00:47:32.586 A:middle
and what the quality of
the final work product was.

00:47:36.996 --> 00:47:39.306 A:middle
And so that's "Let's
Try 2% Darker,"

00:47:39.466 --> 00:47:48.506 A:middle
and the lesson is iterating
quickly leads to better work.

00:47:48.506 --> 00:47:50.616 A:middle
Okay, story number eight.

00:47:52.516 --> 00:47:54.876 A:middle
Three lessons from
making this session.

00:47:55.156 --> 00:47:59.486 A:middle
And so this is not
the original session.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:48:00.196 --> 00:48:02.826 A:middle
I wrote an entirely
different set of slides.

00:48:03.336 --> 00:48:05.526 A:middle
And not only that.

00:48:05.526 --> 00:48:07.506 A:middle
I did three full
rehearsals with them.

00:48:07.506 --> 00:48:10.006 A:middle
I like to rehearse a lot
before, I mean it's important

00:48:10.036 --> 00:48:12.186 A:middle
that this session
goes well for you all.

00:48:12.186 --> 00:48:13.626 A:middle
You all came here, and I want

00:48:13.626 --> 00:48:15.206 A:middle
to make sure they're
giving you a good product,

00:48:15.206 --> 00:48:17.356 A:middle
I mean so I put a
tremendous amount of effort

00:48:17.356 --> 00:48:19.036 A:middle
into preparing the
slides and rehearsing.

00:48:19.636 --> 00:48:23.386 A:middle
And so with that other set of
slides I used up a big portion

00:48:23.386 --> 00:48:26.116 A:middle
of my time rehearsing
that set of slides.

00:48:26.196 --> 00:48:30.506 A:middle
See, the good thing was, it
